Lagos State – A student of the Lagos State University has been reported to have died while he was reading for his exams. In what will come across as a really shocking developmet, a Law student of the Lagos State University has allegedly died in a startling manner. Local reports show that the student passed away while he was reading for his forthcoming exam. Identified as Hilary, the student was found dead, this morning, August 26th, inside the Faculty of Law’s common room. According to his colleagues, the death may be linked to excessive night reading and consumption of caffeine-based stimulants that prevent sleep. The V.C of the institution has already ordered the common room locked. Source